      • getOrderedKeyInfoList

        public java.util.List<DependentKeyInfo> getOrderedKeyInfoList()
        Returns the keys of this object as a list ordered by sortOrder. This is a true copy of the key stored internally. Only Keys marked with 'indicatorField = false' are returned.

      • getIndicatorField

        public DependentKeyInfo getIndicatorField(boolean includeValidIndicator)
        This method returns the xPath name of the indicator field of the dependent object. If there is no such field then null is returned. The returned object is a true copy of the indicator field. If the parameter includeValidIndicator is set to TRUE then the valid indicator list is returned as well otherwise it is not returned.

        See description
